/-
# Phase 6: assembling `MImBound` — the y-orbit dispatch

`floor_kcombo` dispatches an arbitrary `ker ∂₂` class `kcombo c` over its 64 free-cell values:
the zero class is vacuous (`seamC 0 = 0`, so the coset is a boundary, contradicting the
hypothesis), and each of the 63 nonzero classes is a `(0,k)`-translate of one of the 13 y-orbit
representatives (`MImFloorY0`..`MImFloorY12`), whose floor transports via `floor_shiftYk_combo`
(`MImTransport §16`).  `mimBound_holds` then reduces any `ζ ∈ ker ∂₂` to `kcombo` form
(`kerBasis_spans`) and applies the dispatch — discharging the last assumed `Prop` of the
Gross `[[144,12,12]]` distance proof.  Generated by `experiments/bb_lab/scripts/gen_assembly.py`.
-/
